{
	"info": {
		"_postman_id": "30e67384-f5bf-442f-b093-5257bf797c91",
		"name": "DocumentAtom",
		"description": "DocumentAtom v3.0 API Collection.\n\nAll atom extraction requests use the JSON envelope format:\n```json\n{\n  \"Settings\": { ... } | null,\n  \"Data\": \"<base64-encoded-file-data>\"\n}\n```\n\nWhen `Settings` is `null`, the server uses default processor settings for the target type.\n\nTo encode a file as base64 in Postman, use a pre-request script:\n```js\nconst fs = require('fs');\nconst fileData = fs.readFileSync('/path/to/your/file');\npm.collectionVariables.set('base64_data', fileData.toString('base64'));\n```\n\nOr encode via command line:\n- Linux/macOS: `base64 -i file.pdf`\n- Windows PowerShell: `[Convert]::ToBase64String([IO.File]::ReadAllBytes('file.pdf'))`",
		"schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json",
		"_exporter_id": "720438"
	},
